    "DefaultText": "Fishpond"
  },
  "CardDescription": {
    "ParentObjectID": "water_sawmill_fishpond_filled",
    "LocalizationKey": "Water_Sawmill_FishpondFilled_CardDescription",
    "DefaultText": "A young fishpond with a small starter population of pike, perch, and minnow. Only those three breed; trout, char, and sturgeon can be stocked but do not breed. Once the total population exceeds ten the pond becomes Stocked and frogs move in."
  },
  "CardHelpSection": {
    "ParentObjectID": "water_sawmill_fishpond_filled",
    "LocalizationKey": "Water_Sawmill_FishpondFilled_CardHelpSection",
    "DefaultText": "<b>Catch fish:</b> Use Catch Pike / Catch Perch / Catch Minnow / Catch Trout / Catch Char / Catch Sturgeon with a spear nearby.\n\n<b>Fill bowl:</b> Drag an empty water container onto the pond to draw unsafe water.\n\n<b>Stocking:</b> Pike, perch, and minnow grow slowly toward a cap of 10. Trout, char, and sturgeon are tracked separately (cap 10 each) and do not breed. Once the breeding population (pike+perch+minnow) is above 10 the pond promotes to Stocked and frogs become available.\n\n<b>Winter:</b> The pond freezes solid in winter and only ice fishing remains."
  },
